This paper discusses the issue of bloat and over-fitting in Genetic Programming, which is a subfield of Machine Learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses different techniques used by the GP research community to deal with bloat, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the performance of different bloat control methods on different problems, which can be categorized under Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Software Engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper aims to improve the generalization ability of GP solutions, which can be categorized under Systems and Control (cs.SY).
